          <lastSummaryUpdateDate>2019-03-21T20:33:04Z</lastSummaryUpdateDate>
          <text><![CDATA[<p><b>Appalachian Energy and Manufacturing Infrastructure Revitalization Act</b></p> <p>This bill authorizes the Department of Energy and the Department of Commerce to designate an Appalachian regional energy hub project as a critical energy infrastructure project eligible for expedited federal permitting. The bill defines &quot;Appalachian regional energy hub&quot; as a hub that is for natural gas and natural gas liquids, including storage and associated pipelines, and located in the region comprised of Kentucky, Ohio, Pennsylvania, and West Virginia.)</p>]]></text>
          <updateDate>2017-06-12T04:00:00Z</updateDate>
          <name>Introduced in Senate</name>
        </item>
